cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper introduces an extension of linear logic with features from hybrid logic to develop a new typed process framework. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses a new framework for message-passing concurrency and introduces domain-aware multiparty session types. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility because the paper discusses the logical foundations of the new framework and how it ensures session fidelity, global progress, and termination. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility because the paper discusses message-passing concurrency and how processes only communicate with accessible domains. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possibility because the paper discusses the development of a precise analysis of multiparty protocols and how they can be reasoned about at the right level of abstraction.
